{{Other uses|Accident on the Rampe de Laffrey (disambiguation){{!}}Accident on the Rampe de Laffrey}}

In an '''accident on the Rampe de Laffrey''' on April 2, 1975, 29 [[pilgrim]]s from [[Sully-sur-Loire]] in [[Loiret]] were killed when their [[bus]] lost its [[brake]]s at the bottom of the [[Rampe de Laffrey|road]], causing it to fly over a ravine at a speed estimated at 120 kilometers an hour; it then crashed into a [[garden]] and overturned.  The accident came on the heels of [[Accident on the Rampe de Laffrey (1973)|one in 1973]] that killed 43, and was very similar to one that occurred along the same road [[Accident on the Rampe de Laffrey (1946)|in 1946]], killing 18.

As a result of this crash, more careful regulation of electronic braking systems was instituted across [[France]], as were annual inspections of heavy vehicles.<ref name=Laffrey>[http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/actualites/societe/20070722.OBS7710/laffrey__une_descente_meurtriere.html?idfx=RSS_societe Laffrey : une descente meurtrière, ACCIDENT DE CAR<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

