The '''North European Zone Formula 3 Cup''', also known as the '''NEZ Formula 3 Cup''', is an [[open wheel racing]] series based in Northern Europe. The series ran from 2008 to 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fia-nez.eu/pdf/minutes/nez_minutes_2009-02.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-03-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720162548/http://www.fia-nez.eu/pdf/minutes/nez_minutes_2009-02.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-20 |df= }}</ref> The NEZ member counties are Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Iceland, Lithuania, Latvia, Norway, Russia and Sweden.
==Scoring system== In each two race of the weekend, points are awarded to the top twelve finishers, with 25 points for a win. A bonus point is awarded for the fastest qualifying time and for the fastest lap of each race. The same scoring system is used in all FIA NEZ racing championships and cups.
